name: WSJ
text:
RT @JoannaStern: We are all going to die. 

Before we do, we should think about the tech we leave behind to tell our stories + what will happen to our digital stuff. 

That's what my new documentary, "E-ternal: A Tech Quest to 'Live' Forever," is about. 

FULL FILM HERE: https://t.co/thh2UuLsa2 https://t.co/XcZuvIV5Xn

text: Normally, researchers would take years and finish animal testing before injecting any vaccine doses into a human. Pfizer didn’t have that kind of time. Here's the story behind the fastest vaccine approval. https://t.co/xBAF2TpyrN

name: WSJ
text: Elon Musk likened California to a sports team with a long winning streak: “They do tend to get a little complacent, a little entitled, and then they don’t win the championship anymore.” https://t.co/05DvhxqYpI
